Interface UnstratifiedProgram

All Known Subinterfaces:
StratifiedProgram
public interface UnstratifiedProgram
A Datalog program for which each rule and initial fact has been independently validated, but the program as a whole has not been validated. That is, it guarantees that each clause of a program is independently valid, but says nothing about whether the clauses taken together make sense. This might be a concern for language features such as negation, where certain dependencies between clauses are undesirable.
